olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 pear
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet mixed sesame seeds
1 tsp rice wine vinegar
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet beef strips
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 drizzle sesame oil
1 packet Crispy Shallots
1 packet Korean Stir-Fry Sauce

• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice pear. Roughly chop salad leaves.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast mixed sesame seeds,
tossing, until golden, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl and set aside.
• In a small bowl, combine Korean stir-fry sauce, the rice wine vinegar,
garlic, ginger paste and a splash of water. Set aside.

• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook beef strips, in batches, until browned and cooked
through, 1-2 minutes.
• Transfer beef back to the pan (along with any resting juices), then add
Korean sauce mixture and cook until slightly reduced and fragrant,
1 minute.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over high heat helps it stay tender.

• To the toasted sesame seeds, add slaw mix, pear, salad leaves,
mayonnaise, the sesame oil and a drizzle of rice wine vinegar. Toss to
combine and season to taste.

• Divide sesame pear slaw between plates. Top with Korean glazed beef.
• Garnish with crispy shallots to serve.